    public interface UiWidgetMultiComposite<CHILD extends UiWidget>
extends UiWidgetComposite<CHILD>
    This is the abstract interface for a composite widget that can contain multiple children and allows to #re.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)

    • Method Detail

      • removeChild

        boolean removeChild(CHILD child)
        This method removes the given child from this panel.
        Parameters:
        child - is the UiWidget to remove from this panel.
        Returns:
        true if the given child has been removed successfully, false otherwise (it has NOT been previously added).
        See Also:
        List.remove(Object)

      • removeChild

        CHILD removeChild(int index)
        This method removes the child at the given index from this panel.
        Parameters:
        index - is the index of the child to remove. It has to be in the range from 0 to UiWidgetAbstractComposite.getChildCount() - 1.
        Returns:
        the removed child that has previously been at the given index.
        See Also:
        List.remove(int)
